.TH "drm_get_edid" 9 "drm_get_edid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_get_edid \- get EDID data, if available
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct edid *" drm_get_edid
.BI "(struct drm_connector *connector "  ","
.BI "struct i2c_adapter *adapter "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "connector" 12
connector we're probing
.IP "adapter" 12
I2C adapter to use for DDC
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Poke the given I2C channel to grab EDID data if possible.  If found,
attach it to the connector.
.SH "RETURN"
Pointer to valid EDID or NULL if we couldn't find any.
